        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-08 03:57:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI think this looks mostly good.\nI have some doubts about 32 bit clients, I plan to read again that code later on.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "677675a7ce324c3643b07d0f0e0c0a05af7687e7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-04-08 04:20:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI can work on 32-bit client, because my test environment is just 32-bit client :) But compared with 64-bit client, it is more possible to hit dir entry hash collision issues.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "e77c215ded011fa8aecdaa82c668482cafd60c9b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2011-04-08 08:11:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nI think it is still important to work on the 2.x server-side fix for this problem as well.\n\nWe could use the lack of OBD_CONNECT_FULL20 flag to detect older 1.x clients, so that only 32-bit hash values are sent from the MDS.  However this would also mean in order to allow 1.8 clients with the full 64-bit hash value to use OBD_CONNECT_FULL20 they would also need to implement the fixed ptlrpc buffer hashing (commit 30dda5e6), and ensure that the obdo.o_gr field was always initialized to 0 (so ost_validate_obdo() works correctly with 1.8 clients).\n\nAnother option would be to use a new OBD_CONNECT_64BITHASH flag to distinguish these clients.  This might be OK for the 2.1 code since it hasn't really gone into production anywhere.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "56d2521188b9c40e115d9efee038e60649a6b03d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-04-18 20:04:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe patch for 2.x server-side is as following:\n\nhttp://review.whamcloud.com/#change,432",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a197c1af9398750430b345e70f6588994effaf11",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
