      },
      "date": "2011-05-25 03:11:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: (1 inline comment)\n\nPlease see comments for master version of this patch.\n\nI don't think it makes sense for ll_dir_seek() to return inode->i_size for the SEEK_END offset value on a 2.x directory, since that cannot be used as input for SEEK_SET or SEEK_CUR on a hash-offset directory.",
